azy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-131\" title=\"\" src=\"http:\/\/nazitunnels.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/04\/scrivener-2-300x193.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"193\" srcset=\"http:\/\/nazitunnels.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/04\/scrivener-2-300x193.png 300w, http:\/\/nazitunnels.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/04\/scrivener-2-1024x662.png 1024w, http:\/\/nazitunnels.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/04\/scrivener-2.png 1392w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>As you can see, I&#8217;ve been working on my outlines for the first two chapters. I was worried about integration with Zotero, but found <a href=\"http:\/\/www.confectious.net\/thinking\/archives\/2011\/03\/integrating-zot.html\">this tip<\/a> to be helpful. It&#8217;s a bit of a process, but sure beats doing all citations by hand.<\/p>\n<h3>Funding Update<\/h3>\n<p>Also, for an update, I have now applied to two big fellowships, USHMM and the GHI, with one more to go at the National Archives. I should hear back about the USHMM this month.<\/p>\n<p>After that, it&#8217;s the big two, the Fulbright and the DAAD.<\/p>\n<h3>Sources Update<\/h3>\n<p>I have most of the documents scanned from USHMM. There are still a bunch of microfilms I should get digitized from the National Archives (or the originals from the German Archives). Now I just need to start going through them and translating and organizing. I&#8217;ll have a post on that later.<\/p>\n<figure id=\"attachment_132\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-132\" style=\"width: 300px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http:\/\/nazitunnels.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/04\/A4-Hadmersleben-detail.jpg\" data-rel=\"lightbox-image-2\" data-rl_title=\"\" data-rl_caption=\"\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-132\" title=\"\" src=\"http:\/\/nazitunnels.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2011\/04\/A4-Hadmersleben-detail-300x242.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" he